		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2023"></a><br><code>sle2023/paper11</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2023</a> paper:</span><br><i>Cross-Level Debugging for Static Analysers</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MatsVanMolle.html">Mats Van Molle</a>, <a href="../profile/BramVandenbogaerde.html">Bram Vandenbogaerde</a>, <a href="../profile/CoenDeRoover.html">Coen De Roover</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3623476.3623512">10.1145/3623476.3623512</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> The contribution targets debugging of static analysers, which are formal-methods-style tools that compute sound/terminating program properties.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The work provides tooling support to debug the analyser implementation by relating analysis-level and program-level executions.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> It aims to improve the developer experience of diagnosing and fixing bugs in static analysis tools via better debugging support.
</li></ul></li></ul>
